I"<h1 id="oculus-prime-slam-navigator">Oculus Prime SLAM Navigator</h1>

<p>Oculus Prime SLAM Navigator is a low cost, open-source autonomous mobile robot available from <a href="http://www.xaxxon.com/oculusprime/slamnavigator">Xaxxon Technologies</a>, ready for ROS applications. It packs a full mini-ITX motherboard, pre-loaded with Linux Xubuntu 16.04 and ROS Kinetic.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Auto-docking charging station</li>
  <li>Orbbec Astra depth camera</li>
  <li>Servo-tilting camera and lights</li>
  <li>4 wheel gearmotors including encoder</li>
  <li>Precision odometry linear/rotational</li>
  <li>Xaxxon MALG motor/audio/lights/gyro Arduino compatible controller PCB</li>
  <li>4-hour LiPo battery</li>
  <li>Wifi connectivity, overlapping network auto-switching</li>
  <li>3G/4G/LTE connectivity relay server</li>
  <li>Integrated battery charging and power management</li>
  <li>Internet tele-operation web UI</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/img/robots/oculus-prime/oculusprime_charging.jpg" alt="Oculus Prime Charging" /></p>

<p>Please check out <a href="http://www.xaxxon.com/oculusprime/slamnavigator">xaxxon.com</a> for more info and pricing</p>

